A 404 error is an HTTP error code which means that the file requested by the user cannot be found. In your case it means that one of your visitors entered a wrong URL in the address bar, or that you or another website has a dead link. When possible, the referrer is shown so you can find the page/site which contains the dead link. trans-unit.source: When managing a website, it is important to keep track of the software used by visitors so as to be sure that the site displays the same way for everyone. However, because you may end up adding advanced features to your website or even modifying the core PrestaShop code, these additions may not be accessible to everyone.
